461
00:16:30,200 --> 00:16:31,720
It's all for you.

462
00:16:33,159 --> 00:16:33,840
Th-this—

463
00:16:35,559 --> 00:16:37,120
Why are you crying now?

464
00:16:37,919 --> 00:16:38,759
No, sis—

465
00:16:38,919 --> 00:16:39,759
You worked too hard.

466
00:16:40,279 --> 00:16:41,159
I'm so touched.

467
00:16:42,799 --> 00:16:44,039
You kid—

468
00:16:45,240 --> 00:16:46,759
With your grateful heart,

469
00:16:46,879 --> 00:16:48,480
I'm already very moved.

470
00:16:49,080 --> 00:16:50,320
Don't cry, it's okay.

471
00:16:51,559 --> 00:16:52,240
I'm hanging up.

472
00:16:58,799 --> 00:16:59,720
Fight monsters.

473
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:00,679
Worked too hard.

474
00:17:12,960 --> 00:17:14,680
This is the office area.

475
00:17:15,480 --> 00:17:16,759
Usually, with your colleagues,

476
00:17:16,799 --> 00:17:18,039
get along well with everyone.

477
00:17:18,079 --> 00:17:19,079
Learn more from others.

478
00:17:19,880 --> 00:17:20,960
Don't always stand with your hands behind your back.

479
00:17:20,960 --> 00:17:22,359
Are you acting like a boss here?

480
00:17:23,440 --> 00:17:24,680
Be a bit more humble.

481
00:17:25,160 --> 00:17:26,400
Up ahead is the break room.

482
00:17:26,519 --> 00:17:28,000
There's tea and coffee.

483
00:17:28,119 --> 00:17:29,480
You can have cold or hot water.

484
00:17:29,880 --> 00:17:31,440
This is the copy room.

485
00:17:31,720 --> 00:17:32,519
If you have any documents

486
00:17:32,519 --> 00:17:34,000
to print or copy, do it here.

487
00:17:34,240 --> 00:17:35,599
This is the general manager's office.

488
00:17:35,599 --> 00:17:36,000
You—

489
00:17:41,759 --> 00:17:43,720
What are you doing here?

490
00:17:45,279 --> 00:17:45,680
Sis.

491
00:17:47,359 --> 00:17:47,759
Sis, look.

492
00:17:47,759 --> 00:17:48,440
What are you doing?

493
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:50,119
ID photo.

494
00:17:51,680 --> 00:17:53,519
Can you do something serious?

495
00:17:53,599 --> 00:17:55,400
Do you know how hard it was

496
00:17:55,400 --> 00:17:56,559
to get this job here?

497
00:17:56,680 --> 00:17:57,200
I know.

498
00:17:57,839 --> 00:17:58,759
You know?

499
00:17:58,759 --> 00:17:59,400
Yeah.

500
00:17:59,640 --> 00:18:00,920
There were so many people

501
00:18:00,920 --> 00:18:01,640
competing for this position with me.

502
00:18:01,839 --> 00:18:03,319
Do you know why I stood out?

503
00:18:03,359 --> 00:18:03,960
Do you know?

504
00:18:05,039 --> 00:18:05,559
Why?

505
00:18:06,079 --> 00:18:06,759
It's because

506
00:18:06,920 --> 00:18:07,880
I didn't write my resume

507
00:18:07,960 --> 00:18:09,720
the traditional way like you did.

508
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:10,720
My resume

509
00:18:10,799 --> 00:18:11,599
was unique.

510
00:18:11,759 --> 00:18:13,559
So the boss valued my talent.

511
00:18:13,839 --> 00:18:14,839
That's why at work

512
00:18:14,960 --> 00:18:16,880
I can't just follow the rules like you.

513
00:18:17,160 --> 00:18:18,799
Otherwise, I'd just become

514
00:18:18,839 --> 00:18:20,240
an ordinary corporate slave.

515
00:18:21,039 --> 00:18:22,000
Wait, who are you talking about?

516
00:18:22,160 --> 00:18:23,359
Of course, I don't mean you, sis.

517
00:18:23,519 --> 00:18:25,079
Don't call me sis.

518
00:18:27,720 --> 00:18:28,319
Sis.

519
00:18:29,400 --> 00:18:31,079
Everyone else is working overtime.

520
00:18:31,200 --> 00:18:32,279
But you two are just arguing here.

521
00:18:32,680 --> 00:18:33,799
I heard you from far away.

522
00:18:33,960 --> 00:18:34,839
Chattering nonstop.

523
00:18:36,079 --> 00:18:36,839
Xiao Li, who is this?

524
00:18:37,200 --> 00:18:38,079
You know my name is Xiao Li?

525
00:18:38,079 --> 00:18:38,680
This is my sis.

526
00:18:39,680 --> 00:18:40,680
I'm Xiao Li.

527
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:44,599
This is our company's new assistant.

528
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:46,519
I'm showing him around.

529
00:18:47,920 --> 00:18:49,279
This kid is really sweet-talking.

530
00:18:49,359 --> 00:18:50,319
Calls everyone "sis."

531
00:18:50,799 --> 00:18:51,279
Really?

532
00:18:51,279 --> 00:18:52,039
No, auntie.

533
00:18:53,400 --> 00:18:53,960
Not sis.

534
00:18:54,720 --> 00:18:55,119
You—

535
00:18:55,119 --> 00:18:55,920
Hurry up and go.

536
00:18:55,920 --> 00:18:56,680
Stop messing around here.

537
00:18:56,759 --> 00:18:57,440
Go to work now.

538
00:18:57,440 --> 00:18:57,920
Time to work.

539
00:18:58,079 --> 00:18:59,160
Hurry up, it's busy.

540
00:18:59,799 --> 00:19:00,960
Get to work, get to work.

541
00:19:17,720 --> 00:19:19,400
Didn't I tell you this was the third draft?

542
00:19:19,720 --> 00:19:21,519
Why did you send the fourth draft to the boss?

543
00:19:22,039 --> 00:19:22,839
It's the fourth draft.

544
00:19:23,160 --> 00:19:23,880
I revised one draft.

545
00:19:23,880 --> 00:19:24,640
So it's the fourth draft.

546
00:19:24,920 --> 00:19:26,480
Why does an assistant get to change my design?

547
00:19:26,720 --> 00:19:27,079
No—

548
00:19:27,160 --> 00:19:27,599
An assistant

549
00:19:27,759 --> 00:19:29,480
is supposed to help fix what's unreasonable.

550
00:19:31,519 --> 00:19:31,960
Um—

551
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:32,880
Sorry, sorry.

552
00:19:33,079 --> 00:19:33,920
I need you for something urgent.

553
00:19:33,920 --> 00:19:34,279
Come.

554
00:19:34,480 --> 00:19:34,920
Sorry.

555
00:19:34,920 --> 00:19:35,759
Hurry, hurry.

556
00:19:40,599 --> 00:19:41,319
What are you doing over there?

557
00:19:41,599 --> 00:19:42,319
Designing.

558
00:19:42,319 --> 00:19:43,319
Isn't this a design company?

559
00:19:44,079 --> 00:19:45,920
What kind of design is that?

560
00:19:46,240 --> 00:19:48,400
Colleagues are already stressed working overtime.

561
00:19:48,400 --> 00:19:50,039
Don't make things worse.

562
00:19:50,359 --> 00:19:50,759
No—

563
00:19:51,119 --> 00:19:53,160
The boss picked me out of thousands.

564
00:19:53,160 --> 00:19:53,960
For what reason?

565
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:55,839
Just to have me print documents every day?

566
00:19:56,200 --> 00:19:57,920
He must want me to lead a big project.

567
00:19:58,079 --> 00:19:59,599
You even burn instant noodles.

568
00:19:59,599 --> 00:20:01,039
And you want to lead a project?

569
00:20:01,160 --> 00:20:01,880
I've already led one.

570
00:20:02,680 --> 00:20:04,160
I've sent out the company's guidelines.

571
00:20:04,240 --> 00:20:05,200
I've already distributed them.

572
00:20:05,920 --> 00:20:06,759
What guidelines?

573
00:20:07,119 --> 00:20:08,559
I posted them in the group, didn't you see?

574
00:20:08,960 --> 00:20:10,240
I even tagged everyone.

575
00:20:11,240 --> 00:20:12,720
Can you check the group promptly at work?

576
00:20:20,519 --> 00:20:21,839
Delete it right now.

577
00:20:22,440 --> 00:20:23,079
Why delete it?

578
00:20:24,079 --> 00:20:25,119
I get what you mean.

579
00:20:25,359 --> 00:20:26,039
Don't worry.

580
00:20:26,160 --> 00:20:27,559
If I become a department head,

581
00:20:27,720 --> 00:20:28,799
I'll promote you first.

582
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:30,480
